            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think it’s worth pointing out that on Windows, `npx` is essentially `npx.cmd`, so it is ultimately parsed by `cmd.exe`.\n\n---\n\nEdit: Maybe we should consider improving `build_cmd_line()` by checking whether `argv[0]` is a cmd target and quoting if some special characters are detected. Maybe that would make list-form jobstart() behave normally for Windows.",
