        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Ah, this is another interesting and legitimate case. When invoking a `.cmd/.bat` file directly (i.e. `npx` here), Windows implicitly translates it into\n```cmd\ncmd.exe /c \"\"npx\" -y qrcode-terminal hello&world\"\n```\nAt that point, `&` is interpreted as a separator and `world` is treated as a separate command.\n\nI ran into a similar case while investigating the [BatBadBut](https://flatt.tech/research/posts/batbadbut-you-cant-securely-execute-commands-on-windows) part  for PR https://github.com/libuv/libuv/pull/5096:\n<img height=\"200\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/60fc5946-00e3-45e4-b10c-a8aca2a15480\" />\n\nBTW, the actual escaping might be fairly complex, though I'm not entirely sure yet—still looking into how other languages handle it for reference, such as `Node/Go/Rust/PHP/Haskell`. This might end up affecting this issue as well, so dropping it here for visibility. :)\n\n",
            "created_at": "2026-03-27T10:41:26Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38470#issuecomment-4141710114",
